<p>Everybody knows that apple announced new feature to block ad in safari.</p>  <p>I've created a simple page with such html-source:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;html&gt;test1&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://www.google.ru/logos/doodles/2015/googles-17th-birthday-6231962352091136-hp.png"&gt;&lt;br&gt;test2&lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Then in xcode 7.1 I created a new target of type "Content Blocker", now I'm watching at <strong>blockerList.json</strong> file</p>  <p>I found only <a href="https://www.hackingwithswift.com/safari-content-blocking-ios9" rel="nofollow">this</a> article about content blocker developing where I've red that <strong>url-filter</strong> is a regular expression.  So I tried a bit to block my image but did not satisfied with result: image do not dissappear.</p>  <p>I tried:</p>  <pre><code>"url-filter": ".*google.ru\/logos\/"  "url-filter": "(.*?)google.ru\/logos\/(.*?)"  "url-filter": "&lt;img src="(.*?)google.ru\/logos\/(.*?)\"" </code></pre>  <p>When I'm running my app xcode asks me which app I want to run</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/quEJm.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/quEJm.png" alt=""></a></p>  <p>I'm always selecting Safari. Not sure if changes I'm making in blockerList.json reloads to Safari but help me with this please.</p>  <p>So question is how to block image printed such as in html-source example at the begginnig of this post. Thanks.</p>  <p><strong>Update</strong></p>  <p>I've a short video about my doings: <a href="https://youtu.be/t6_i33BAlRE" rel="nofollow">https://youtu.be/t6_i33BAlRE</a></p>